      "comment": "TOTAL TEXAS (7) jumped from the inside and boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten 1.5 lengths (22.70) behind Cha Cha Ethics at Maitland. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Winning claims. KIANDO PIPER (8) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where she gave a sight, finishing third (25.38) and beaten 4.5 lengths over 431m at Gunnedah. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Expecting another good run. BOBBIN' BRUNO (2) jumped from the squeeze on debut and finished well back at this track over 516m (30.75). Much improved and rates a winning chance. CREEPING SOX (1) has not raced over this journey but still warrants respect.",
